RT @LomahCrypto: I think these sort of longer awkward choppy conditions in an uptrend shake the most people out.

Give people too much time to sit in their positions and they'll likely find or come up with new reasons to justify selling without their invalidations being hit.

It's partially why you see so many bullish at range highs and bearish at range lows.

rawContent:
Anytime I make a post about Tether, I get dozens of Bitcoin maxis and paid China bots in the comments raging at me, claiming it’s fully backed and legit.

This goes to show you how unprepared the crypto community is. The overwhelming majority do NOT know the risks of Tether and centralized scam exchanges. 

They’ve been brainwashed into thinking everything is perfectly fine, all the ETFs will be approved, CZ and SBF are just innocent angels and BTC is on its way to organically hit $1,000,000 by next month. 

That’s fine, we tried warning them, but it’s up to them whether they choose to follow the hard facts or the comforting lies. Many will get rekt when the music stops soon and the bear market continues. 

When we last time warned at $68K in 2021, we had the exact same reaction and time proved that we one of the only pages that were correct (93% of the price crash was predicted accurately), the 1% who listened were the only few that survived. The 99% of maxis got rekt. 

The exact same thing was said last year when we predicted a short term bump at $16,000 to over $35,000. This also happened. 

If you want to succeed in this market, my advise is: Don’t be lazy - do your own research, don’t blindly follow the herd, and make timely and non-emotional decisions.

rawContent:
The KyberSwap team has been in contact with the owners of the frontrun bots that extracted about $5.7M* worth of funds from KyberSwap pools on Polygon and Avalanche during the exploit.
We have negotiated with the owners of the frontrun bots to return 90% of the users’ funds taken by them to: 0x8180a5CA4E3B94045e05A9313777955f7518D757,
in return for a 10% bounty as described in this on-chain message: https://t.co/lBQhLvSLcu

So far, a total of about $4.67M** worth of funds has been returned to the KyberSwap Deployer address on Polygon via these transactions:
813,198.63 dBSGG (~$813.2k): https://t.co/52uGofpKMp

361.92 axl-wstETH (~$870.5k): https://t.co/oxSb6QI6ci

441.8 WETH (~$919k): https://t.co/C5H8aCnlIz

261.5 wstETH (~$624k): https://t.co/l0ZGPOmBFb

711,430.9 WMATIC (~$547.8k): https://t.co/hGH3rOuZwr

443,011.6 USDT (~$443k): https://t.co/7Bppz1A1Bg

385,630.7 USDC (~$385.6k): https://t.co/g9H7X5JKv1

65,130 USDT (~$65.1k): https://t.co/tV0bioLwoW

Following this recovery of users’ funds from the frontrun bots, we will continue to support law enforcement and cybersecurity on track down and recovery of users’ funds from the perpetrator of the exploit attack.

*Based on market prices at the time of the exploit
**Based on market prices at the time of this announcement

rawContent:
The anatomy of the recent $BTC move and why I'm being cautious here

Obviously, because it's a solid daily resistance that has been holding for the last couple of weeks.

Orderflow

Starting from the bottom and looking at the blue section of my chart 

Spot (white line) initiated this move being in complete control while leverage shorts were puking on the way up visible from the liquidations and from the closed Open Interest on each spike up.
During this whole up time, Futs (Orange Line) were lacking and trying to catch up. 
Funding was relatively low/neutral; even at the last drop, it briefly went negative. 

Moving to the greenish part of the chat. 
The local top ($37900) was marked with SPOT starting to drop while futs were catching up and even taking control. 
OI started increasing rapidly while the price went nowhere. 
Currently, SPOT losing control and futs keeping the price where it is. 
On every small dip, OI drops and long gets liquidated. 
Positive funding
OI is currently up 7% (~12 000 #BTC )

Indeed there was a solid buy wall between 37400/37200 that was fully filled

I am bullish but not here. 
that's why I've sold 70% of my scalps from the local bottom while keeping all of my swing trades open. 
I am not going short, just trying to explain why opening fresh longs here might be bad for your financials.

.@KyberSwap was exploited due to tick manipulation and double liquidity counting.
In summary, the attackers borrowed a flash loan and drained the pools with low liquidity. rawContent:
Who remembers how CZ Binance would frequently post about "FUD" or "Funds are Safu" whenever something negative was said about him or his company? 

The truth is, most of those accusations were very truthful, and he knows that.

Despite his facade of being such a virtuous prophet in the crypto space, we saw beyond it and warned everyone for years. Turns out, time proved that we were right once again.

Earlier today, CZ publicly confessed to his crimes, admitted he fucked up, pleaded guilty, and is being forced to pay a substantial $50 million personal fine. It's also likely he will also spend several years behind bars in prison.

He has always been a fraudster, although knowing how this space works, it may take some time for his sheep followers to acknowledge this fact. They will just keep perpetuating the "FUD" saying, without any sign of brain function or reasoning.

That being said, fraudsters often attempt to discredit their critics by using tactics like saying they're spreading fear and doubt (FUD). CZ turned this into a sort of movement, where people felt emotionally attacked and connected to him / his company. 

It was a manipulative strategy that ultimately failed. It's crucial for investors to learn from this experience and avoid blindly following others. 

Trust me when I say this, but literally no one cares about spreading "fear, uncertainty, and doubt", it has no impact on anything and fake (bad) news is so easy to spot.

We rather aim on revealing the corrupt origins of these deceptive figures that many people idolize in the crypto industry. It is very important to expose them to allow this space to flourish. They hold everyone back.

rawContent:
It is an honour and with the deepest humility that I step into the role of Binance’s new CEO.

We operate the world's largest cryptocurrency exchange by volume. The trust placed on us by our 150m users and thousands of employees is a responsibility that I take seriously and hold dear.

With CZ, and our leadership team’s support, I have accepted this role so that we can continue to meet and exceed the expectations of stakeholders while achieving our core mission, the freedom of money.

The foundation on which Binance stands today is stronger than ever.

To ensure a bright future, I intend to use everything I’ve learned over the past three decades of financial services and regulatory experience to guide our remarkable, innovative, and committed team.

My focus will be on:

1) reassuring users that they can remain confident in the financial strength, security and safety of the company
2) collaborating with regulators to uphold high standards globally that foster innovation while providing important consumer protections
3) working with partners to drive growth and adoption of Web3

We are here to stay.  Please lend me your support. Excited for the days ahead!

rawContent:
RT @cz_binance: Today, I stepped down as CEO of Binance. Admittedly, it was not easy to let go emotionally. But I know it is the right thing to do. I made mistakes, and I must take responsibility. This is best for our community, for Binance, and for myself.

Binance is no longer a baby. It is time for me to let it walk and run. I know Binance will continue to grow and excel with the deep bench it has.

I’m pleased to announce that @_RichardTeng, our now former Global Head of Regional Markets, has been named the new CEO of Binance today.

Richard is a highly qualified leader and, with over three decades of financial services and regulatory experience, he will navigate the company through its next period of growth. He will ensure Binance delivers on our next phase of security, transparency, compliance, and growth.

Prior to joining Binance, Richard was CEO of the Financial Services Regulatory Authority at Abu Dhabi Global Market (ADGM); Chief Regulatory Officer of the Singapore Exchange (SGX); and Director of Corporate Finance in the Monetary Authority of Singapore.

With Richard and the entire team, I’m confident that the best days for @Binance and the crypto industry lay ahead.

As a shareholder and former CEO with historical knowledge of our company, I will remain available to the team to consult as needed, consistent with the framework set out in our U.S. agency resolutions.

What’s next for me?

I will take a break first. I have not had a single day of real (phone off) break for the last 6 and half years.

After that, my current thinking is I will probably do some passive investing, being a minority token/shareholder in startups in areas of blockchain/Web3/DeFi, AI and biotech. I am happy that I will finally have more time to spend looking at DeFi.

I can’t see myself being a CEO driving a startup again. I am content being an one-shot (lucky) entrepreneur. Should there be listeners, I may be open to being a coach/mentor to a small number of upcoming entrepreneurs, privately. If for nothing else, I can at least tell them what not to do.

On that note, I am proud to point out that in our resolutions with the U.S. agencies they:

- do not allege that Binance misappropriated any user funds, and
- do not allege that Binance engaged in any market manipulation.

Funds are SAFU!

With that, I look forward to seeing the new leadership take the reins. Please join me in congratulating Richard on his well-deserved promotion.

rawContent:
Today, I stepped down as CEO of Binance. Admittedly, it was not easy to let go emotionally. But I know it is the right thing to do. I made mistakes, and I must take responsibility. This is best for our community, for Binance, and for myself.

Binance is no longer a baby. It is time for me to let it walk and run. I know Binance will continue to grow and excel with the deep bench it has.

I’m pleased to announce that @_RichardTeng, our now former Global Head of Regional Markets, has been named the new CEO of Binance today.

Richard is a highly qualified leader and, with over three decades of financial services and regulatory experience, he will navigate the company through its next period of growth. He will ensure Binance delivers on our next phase of security, transparency, compliance, and growth.

Prior to joining Binance, Richard was CEO of the Financial Services Regulatory Authority at Abu Dhabi Global Market (ADGM); Chief Regulatory Officer of the Singapore Exchange (SGX); and Director of Corporate Finance in the Monetary Authority of Singapore.

With Richard and the entire team, I’m confident that the best days for @Binance and the crypto industry lay ahead.

As a shareholder and former CEO with historical knowledge of our company, I will remain available to the team to consult as needed, consistent with the framework set out in our U.S. agency resolutions.

What’s next for me?

I will take a break first. I have not had a single day of real (phone off) break for the last 6 and half years.

After that, my current thinking is I will probably do some passive investing, being a minority token/shareholder in startups in areas of blockchain/Web3/DeFi, AI and biotech. I am happy that I will finally have more time to spend looking at DeFi.

I can’t see myself being a CEO driving a startup again. I am content being an one-shot (lucky) entrepreneur. Should there be listeners, I may be open to being a coach/mentor to a small number of upcoming entrepreneurs, privately. If for nothing else, I can at least tell them what not to do.

On that note, I am proud to point out that in our resolutions with the U.S. agencies they:

- do not allege that Binance misappropriated any user funds, and
- do not allege that Binance engaged in any market manipulation.

Funds are SAFU!

With that, I look forward to seeing the new leadership take the reins. Please join me in congratulating Richard on his well-deserved promotion.

Onwards!

CZ

Essentially, the proposal aims to approve tokens held by the timelock contract to a malicious contract, which has already been blacklisted by the project (https://t.co/6mWKx4kvyr).

The person behind the Indexed Finance governance attack also attempted one on @relevantfeed via 0x9b9 earlier this month.

0x9b9 was funded by Alex Chon an alleged DPRK IT worker who has been fired from at least 2 roles for suspicious behavior.

"B-But you're spreading FUD! The Lightning Network costs only a few cents and is instant!!!"

The Lightning Network is widely criticized as the most centralized scam ever, entirely controlled by BlockStream/Tether.

This network lacks the capacity to handle even a fraction of the transaction volume needed for a small city, let alone the entire global financial system. Moreover, it is widely unrecognized, much like Bitcoin itself...

The claim that the "Lightning Network" is the solution to Bitcoin's failures only highlights the minimal understanding many Bitcoin maximalists possess about the system.

If these maximalists actually delved into the whitepaper and Satoshi's threads (which 99% haven't), they would realize that Satoshi vehemently opposed the Lightning Network and warned against it. 

It was merely a scheme created by maximalist scammers who aim to control the network.
